%N A392154 Left diagonal of the difference table of n! under the operator Delta + 2*Delta^2.
%C A392154 a(n) is the first entry in the n-th row of a triangular array built from the factorial sequence, where T(0,m) = m! and each subsequent row is obtained by T(n,m) = 2*T(n-1,m+2) - 3*T(n-1,m+1) + T(n-1,m).
%C A392154 The rows are generated by iterating the operator Delta_2 = Delta + 2*Delta^2, where Delta is the forward difference operator.
%C A392154 This is the r=2 case of the family Delta_r = Delta + r*Delta^2 associated with inverse Pascal-type matrices (Barry). For r=0 this yields A000166 (derangement numbers). For r=1 this yields A033815.
%H A392154 Paul Barry, <a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/journals/JIS/VOL16/Barry3/barry252.html">On the Inverses of a Family of Pascal-Like Matrices Defined by Riordan Arrays</a>, Journal of Integer Sequences, Vol. 16 (2013), Article 13.5.6.
%H A392154 Dalton Heilig, <a href="https://scholar.rose-hulman.edu/rhumj/vol18/iss2/4">Pascal's triangle in difference tables and an alternate approach to exponential functions</a>, Rose-Hulman Undergrad. Math. J., 18, 2017, 2, Article 4.
%F A392154 a(n) = T(n,0) where T(0,m)=m! and T(n,m) = 2*T(n-1,m+2) - 3*T(n-1,m+1) + T(n-1,m). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Apr 14 2026
%F A392154 a(n) = Sum_{j = 0..n} Sum_{k = 0..n} (-1)^(j+k)*binomial(n,j)*binomial(n,k)*2^j*(j+k)!.
%F A392154 a(n) = Integral_{t = 0..oo} (2*t - 1)^n *(t - 1)^n*exp(-t) dt.
%e A392154 The Delta_2 difference table of n! (left diagonal gives a(m)):
%e A392154   m=0:      1      1      2      6     24    120    720   5040       [n!]
%e A392154   m=1:      2      7     32    174   1104   8040  66240    ...
%e A392154   m=2:     45    259   1718  12942 109464    ...
%e A392154   m=3:   2704  20989 181820    ...
%e A392154   m=4: 303377    ...
